text: Tulcea is a city of Dobrogea in Romania. As of 2002, nearly 92,000 people were living in Tulcea. It is the capital of Tulcea county. == Twinned towns == The following towns are twinned with Tulcea: * Aalborg, Denmark * Rovigo, Italy * Shumen, Bulgaria * Ilion, Greece * Bishopstown, Ireland * Pushkin, Russia == References == == Other websites == *Tulcea City Hall *Tulcea County Prefecture *Tulcea County Council Category:Municipalities of Romania Category:Cities in Romania Category:County capitals of Romania Category:Tulcea County
